  "tcmHistory": {
    "en": "Ginseng has been used in Traditional Chinese Medicine for over 5,000 years. The name \"Panax\" derives from the Greek word for \"all-healing,\" reflecting its reputation as a panacea. Wild ginseng was so valued that it was reserved for emperors and nobility in ancient China.",
    "zh-Hant": "人蔘在中醫藥中已有五千多年歷史。《神農本草經》列為上品，謂「主補五臟，安精神，定魂魄，止驚悸，除邪氣，明目，開心益智。」",
    "zh-Hans": "人参在中医药中已有五千多年历史。《神農本草经》列为上品，謂「主补五脏，安精神，定魂魄，止惊悸，除邪气，明目，开心益智。」"
  },
  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "In TCM, Ginseng (Ren Shen) is classified as a supreme Qi tonic, primarily used to:\n\n- Tonify Yuan (Original) Qi: The foundation of all Qi in the body\n- Strengthen the Spleen and Lung: Improve digestion and respiration\n- Generate body fluids: Especially useful in thirst and dryness\n- Calm the Spirit (Shen): For anxiety, insomnia, and palpitations\n- Rescue from collapse: In critical conditions with fading pulse",
    "zh-Hant": "人蔘大補元氣，復脈固脫，補脾益肺，生津養血，安神益智。用於體虛欲脫、肢冷脈微、脾虛食少、肺虛喘咳、津傷口渴、內熱消渴、氣血虧虛、久病虛羸、驚悸失眠、陽痿宮冷。",
    "zh-Hans": "人参大补元气，復脉固脫，补脾益肺，生津养血，安神益智。用于体虚欲脫、肢冷脉微、脾虚食少、肺虚喘咳、津傷口渴、內热消渴、气血虧虚、久病虚羸、惊悸失眠、阳痿宮冷。"
  },
  "tcmModernResearch": {
    "en": "Contemporary research has identified ginsenosides as the primary active compounds. Studies suggest potential benefits for:\n\n- Cognitive function and memory enhancement\n- Immune system modulation\n- Fatigue reduction and physical performance\n- Blood sugar regulation\n- Cardiovascular health\n- Anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects\n\nClinical trials continue to explore its adaptogenic properties and potential applications in cancer supportive care.",
    "zh-Hant": "【人蔘】Modern Research內容待翻譯補充。",
    "zh-Hans": "【人参】Modern Research內容待翻譯补充。"
  },
  "tcmFunctions": {
    "en": "- Adaptogenic stress support\n- Cognitive enhancement and mental clarity\n- Immune system modulation\n- Energy and vitality support\n- Blood sugar regulation\n- Cardiovascular tonic",
    "zh-Hant": "大補元氣，復脈固脫，補脾益肺，生津養血，安神益智",
    "zh-Hans": "大补元气，復脉固脫，补脾益肺，生津养血，安神益智"
  },
  "tcmSafetyConsideration": {
    "en": "May interact with blood thinners (warfarin), diabetes medications, stimulants, and MAO inhibitors. Not recommended during pregnancy without medical supervision. Avoid in hypertension, acute infections, or excess heat conditions. Long-term high-dose use may cause side effects including insomnia, nervousness, and hypertension.",
    "zh-Hant": "可能與華法林、糖尿病藥物、興奮劑、單胺氧化酶抑制劑相互作用。孕婦慎用。高血壓、急性感染、實熱證者忌用。長期大量服用可能導致失眠、煩躁、血壓升高。"
  },
  "tcmBotanicalSource": {
    "en": "Panax ginseng is a slow-growing perennial herb in the Araliaceae family, native to the mountainous regions of Korea, Northeast China, and far eastern Russia. Wild ginseng is increasingly rare and protected; most commercial supply is cultivated. The plant requires 5-7 years to mature before harvest. The root is the primary medicinal part, characterized by its human-like shape."
  },
  "tcmClassicalReference": {
    "zh-Hant": "《神農本草經》：「人蔘，味甘微寒。主補五臟，安精神，定魂魄，止驚悸，除邪氣，明目，開心益智。久服輕身延年。」"
  },
